# Vision (Template Matching + OCR Text Detection)

## Context

`tests/vision_utils.py` provides image-based localization: template matching (OpenCV) and OCR text search (pytesseract) on screenshots. Used by test_template_matching.py and test_ocr.py; the main bot pipeline uses iframe traversal for Print PDF, not vision.

## Patterns

### Template Matching

- `find_template(screenshot, template, threshold=0.8, scales=SCALES)` → `MatchResult`
- Multi-scale matching (0.5–2.0) handles DPI/resolution differences between reference and live screenshots
- `MatchResult.found` is True when `confidence >= threshold`; `.center` gives click coordinates

### OCR Text Detection

- `find_text_ocr(screenshot, target, crop=OCR_CROP_REGION, ...)` → `OcrMatchResult`
- Pre-processes: crop, grayscale, invert, threshold, scale for white-on-colored text (e.g., button labels)
- `OCR_CROP_REGION` defaults to Print PDF button region `(1250, 150, 1700, 350)`
- Returns coordinates in original screenshot space (adds crop offset to word boxes)

### Debug Helpers

- `highlight_match(screenshot, result, output_path)` — draw rectangle on match
- `highlight_ocr_match(...)` — draw all detected words + highlight match
- `draw_click_marker(...)` — crosshair at click point for visual debugging

## Anti-patterns

- Do not use vision in the main Print PDF flow; iframe traversal is the canonical approach
- Do not assume `find_template` works across all screen densities; use multiple scales
- Do not skip the `crop` parameter for `find_text_ocr` when targeting a known region—narrowing improves accuracy

## Best Practices

- Test fixtures: `tests/example-page.png`, `tests/print-pdf-button.png`; conftest fixtures use `TESTS_DIR`
- If template match fails, add scale factors to `SCALES` or adjust `threshold`
- For OCR on button labels, use `invert=True` and `scale=2.0` for white text on colored backgrounds
